{
  "video_id": "4DQv80biYbs",
  "title": "Why Babies Can't Drink Water",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 340.0,
      "end_time": 2280.0,
      "text": "There is a time in every person's life"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 2280.0,
      "end_time": 4510.0,
      "text": "when drinking water is deadly."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 4510.0,
      "end_time": 8427.0,
      "text": "Even as much as a few ounces is enough to kill."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 13630.0,
      "end_time": 18700.0,
      "text": "The average healthy adult is made up of 55 to 60% water."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 18700.0,
      "end_time": 22390.0,
      "text": "The average baby, on the other hand, is roughly 75% water."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 22390.0,
      "end_time": 25300.0,
      "text": "And that difference is why babies shouldn't drink water"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 25300.0,
      "end_time": 27520.0,
      "text": "before they're at least six months old."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 27520.0,
      "end_time": 30509.0,
      "text": "Not from the tap or a well or a spring."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 30510.0,
      "end_time": 34400.0,
      "text": "Plain water is just plain off limits."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 34400.0,
      "end_time": 36140.0,
      "text": "You see, everyone's kidneys have a limit"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 36140.0,
      "end_time": 38130.0,
      "text": "to how much water they can handle."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 38130.0,
      "end_time": 39960.0,
      "text": "Break that limit, and the excess water"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 39960.0,
      "end_time": 41780.0,
      "text": "will back up into your bloodstream,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 41780.0,
      "end_time": 45220.0,
      "text": "where it dilutes the salt, or sodium, in your blood."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 45220.0,
      "end_time": 49700.0,
      "text": "Once your blood dips below 0.4 ounces of sodium per gallon,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 49700.0,
      "end_time": 52587.0,
      "text": "you're at risk of a condition called Hyponatremia."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 52587.0,
      "end_time": 55190.0,
      "text": "It happens when your cells try to return sodium levels"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 55190.0,
      "end_time": 57610.0,
      "text": "to normal by absorbing the extra water"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 57610.0,
      "end_time": 60350.0,
      "text": "and swell up like a water balloon in the process,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 60350.0,
      "end_time": 63130.0,
      "text": "causing complications like confusion,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 63130.0,
      "end_time": 65560.0,
      "text": "vomiting and muscle spasms."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 65560.0,
      "end_time": 67930.0,
      "text": "Hyponatremia is common in marathon runners"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 67930.0,
      "end_time": 70730.0,
      "text": "who drink too much too fast during a race"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 70730.0,
      "end_time": 72590.0,
      "text": "without also providing enough sodium"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 72590.0,
      "end_time": 74740.0,
      "text": "to balance out their blood."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 74740.0,
      "end_time": 77270.0,
      "text": "And if you keep drinking, that excess water"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 77270.0,
      "end_time": 80729.0,
      "text": "will eventually reach the cells in your brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 80730.0,
      "end_time": 83280.0,
      "text": "By this point, you have a dangerous case"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 83280.0,
      "end_time": 85800.0,
      "text": "of water intoxication, which affects"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 85800.0,
      "end_time": 90110.0,
      "text": "roughly 200,000 Americans each year."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 90110.0,
      "end_time": 92429.0,
      "text": "It occurs when your brain cells swell,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 92430.0,
      "end_time": 95100.0,
      "text": "which builds up pressure inside your skull"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 95100.0,
      "end_time": 97500.0,
      "text": "that can lead to seizures, brain damage,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 97500.0,
      "end_time": 100490.0,
      "text": "and, in severe cases, death."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 100490.0,
      "end_time": 103315.0,
      "text": "But don't worry, dying from water intoxication"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 103333.0,
      "end_time": 106300.0,
      "text": "is extremely hard for a fully-grown human."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 106300.0,
      "end_time": 109730.0,
      "text": "An adult would have to drink 2.5 to 5 gallons"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 109730.0,
      "end_time": 112510.0,
      "text": "every few hours to reach that point."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 112510.0,
      "end_time": 115470.0,
      "text": "But for newborns, it's a different story."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 115470.0,
      "end_time": 118550.0,
      "text": "Their kidneys are about half the size of an adult's,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 118550.0,
      "end_time": 121399.0,
      "text": "so they can't hold much water to begin with."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 121400.0,
      "end_time": 125460.0,
      "text": "And it takes just a few ounces to cause problems."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 125460.0,
      "end_time": 128769.0,
      "text": "On top of that, their kidneys aren't developed enough yet"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 128770.00000000001,
      "end_time": 131730.0,
      "text": "to properly filter water, so any water"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 131730.0,
      "end_time": 135340.0,
      "text": "that enters their body ends up in the circulatory system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 135340.0,
      "end_time": 136810.0,
      "text": "where it dilutes their blood"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 136810.0,
      "end_time": 140730.0,
      "text": "and increases their water content by 7 to 8%."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 140730.0,
      "end_time": 143290.0,
      "text": "But it's not just drinking straight H2O"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 143290.0,
      "end_time": 144920.0,
      "text": "that poses a threat."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 144920.0,
      "end_time": 148869.0,
      "text": "In fact, most cases of water intoxication in infants"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 148870.0,
      "end_time": 151440.0,
      "text": "don't even involve a glass of water."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 151440.0,
      "end_time": 154310.0,
      "text": "A common mistake is when people dilute baby formula"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 154310.0,
      "end_time": 157100.0,
      "text": "too much by accident, or when parents"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 157100.0,
      "end_time": 159530.0,
      "text": "dunk their infants up and down in a swimming pool,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 159530.0,
      "end_time": 163150.0,
      "text": "and in the process the infant gulps in too much water."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 163150.0,
      "end_time": 164610.0,
      "text": "It's important that if your baby"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 164610.0,
      "end_time": 166840.0,
      "text": "is showing signs of water intoxication"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 166840.0,
      "end_time": 169690.0,
      "text": "that you take them to the hospital immediately,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 169690.0,
      "end_time": 172680.0,
      "text": "where a doctor will likely provide some form of fluids"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 172680.0,
      "end_time": 174820.0,
      "text": "like intravenous saline solution"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 174820.0,
      "end_time": 177613.0,
      "text": "to bring the infant's sodium levels up to normal."
    }
  ]
}